commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, `find` will only display `Person`'s whose details
have a full word match for one of the keywords provided by
the user.

Update behaviour to display `Person`'s details so long as
the keywords provided match said details partially.

This will provide the user with some ease of use in terms of
a more flexible search function.

commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, `find` command is not responsive (i.e., results do
not populate until user presses `Enter` key). In this scenario,
allowing a partial keyword search might lead to the user getting
confused.

Hence, this feature is being removed, and will be introduced at
a later iteration when it makes more sense to include it.

commitResults.messageBody:
Code to ensure that user provided a file path referring
to a file and not a directory was introduced in the recent
commit. This caused test cases to fail.

Upon examining the code, it was noted that Java automatically
handles this by treating it as part of the filename or
removing it completely (the behaviour is OS-dependent). Hence, the code
added was removed.
